Patch 4: High-level client.start() auth flow
============================================

Replace the manual sendCode + signIn orchestration with GramJS's
built-in client.start() API, which handles:
- phoneCodeHash management (no more stale hash bugs)
- DC migration (server redirects to different data centers)
- 2FA / SESSION_PASSWORD_NEEDED
- Sign-up flow (AuthorizationSignUpRequired)
- Error recovery with onError callback

The key insight: client.start() uses async callbacks:
  - phoneNumber: async () => "+1234567890"
  - phoneCode: async (isCodeViaApp) => "12345"
  - password: async () => "mypassword"
  - onError: (err) => console.log(err)

We provide Promise-based callbacks that block until the watch user
provides the code/password via the Clay config UI.

